                                Calculator

        Double clicking on the Calculator icon produces a calculator on the
Workbench. It has four function: Add, Subtract, Multiply and Divide. The
buttons on the calculator can be clicked on with the mouse, or like me you
can use the corresponding keys on Amiga keyboard or numerical keypad to
enter your calculation. The key on the keyboard is equivalent to the
= button.

        As well as the standard numerical gadgets from 0 to 9, there are
also the following non - numerical gadgets, which are defined thus:

        CA Clears All. This clears all the previous entries and resets the
calculator to 0.

        CE Clears Entry. This clears the list number you entered, so that
if you make a mistake in the middle of a calculation you needn't start the
whole sum again.

        The Calculator is closed by clicking on the close gadget in the top
left hand corner of the calculator.

        Workbench 3 Calculator...

  Has three menus available....


                Calculator Project Menu

        Clear Entry and Clear All do the same thing as the calculator keys
CE and CA respectively. Quit turns off and exits the calculator.



                Calculator Edit Menu

        This menu contains three items: Cut, Copy and Paste. Cut copies the
current entry in the calculator and clear the display. Copy copies the
current entry without clearing the display. Paste places the last value
that was either cut or copied back into the display.


                Calculator Window Menu

        This menu contains one option, Show Tape. It brings up a window
showing the calculator entries and results. You can copy anything in this
window by drag selecting and pressing Right Amiga Plus the C Key.



